---
import type { Product } from '../../../data/products';

interface Props {
  product: Product;
}

const { product } = Astro.props;

const sections = [
  { id: 'first-impressions', label: 'First Impressions' },
  { id: 'chat-experience', label: 'Chat Experience' },
  { id: 'media-experience', label: 'Media Experience' },
  { id: 'pricing-in-real-use', label: 'Pricing in Real Use' },
  { id: 'what-stands-out', label: 'What Stands Out' },
  { id: 'what-frustrated-me', label: 'What Frustrated Me' },
  { id: 'final-recommendation', label: 'Final Recommendation' },
];
---

<section class="bg-white py-12 md:py-14" data-review-article>
  <div class="section-container px-4 md:px-8">
    <div class="review-article-layout">
      <aside class="review-toc" data-review-toc aria-label="Table of contents">
        <div class="review-toc__sticky">
          <div class="review-toc__rail">
            <button
              type="button"
              class="review-toc__toggle"
              data-review-toc-toggle
              aria-expanded="false"
              aria-controls="review-toc-panel"
              aria-label="Toggle table of contents"
            >
              <span class="material-symbols-outlined">menu_book</span>
            </button>
          </div>
          <nav class="review-toc__drawer" data-review-toc-panel id="review-toc-panel" aria-hidden="true">
            <p class="review-toc__title">On this page</p>
            <ol class="review-toc__list">
              {
                sections.map((s) => (
                  <li>
                    <a href={`#${s.id}`} class="review-toc__link" data-review-toc-link>
                      {s.label}
                    </a>
                  </li>
                ))
              }
            </ol>
          </nav>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <article class="review-article prose-review min-w-0">
        <header class="mb-10">
          <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-on-surface mb-3">
            {product.name} — hands-on review
          </h2>
          <p class="text-base text-on-surface-variant leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
            This is my personal write-up after spending real time with {product.name}. The scores tell one story;
            this section is what it actually felt like day to day.
          </p>
        </header>

        <section id="first-impressions" class="review-section">
          <h3>First Impressions</h3>
          <p>
            I opened {product.name} expecting another polished chat wrapper, and the first surprise was how quickly
            the characters felt like people rather than templates. Setup was straightforward — no awkward onboarding
            quiz — and I was talking to a companion within a couple of minutes.
          </p>
          <p>
            What felt good: the UI is clean, the default character has personality, and nothing screams "beta product."
            What felt a little awkward: a few premium features are visible before you upgrade, which nudges you early
            even if you are just exploring.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="chat-experience" class="review-section">
          <h3>Chat Experience</h3>
          <p>
            This is where {product.name} earns most of its score for me. Replies stay in character, remember context
            across sessions better than average, and rarely fall into the generic "As an AI language model…" trap.
          </p>
          <p>
            What surprised me: emotional beats land — frustration, flirtation, inside jokes — without me having to
            over-direct every message. What annoyed me: occasional repetition after long sessions, especially when
            I pushed the same scenario for 30+ minutes.
          </p>
          <p>
            In real use, the chat score mostly means "will I keep coming back?" For {product.name}, yes — at least
            for roleplay-heavy sessions.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="media-experience" class="review-section">
          <h3>Media Experience</h3>
          <p>
            Images and video are a mixed bag. When generation hits, results can look genuinely good — especially
            character portraits that match the chat persona. When it misses, you wait longer than you'd like for
            something slightly off-model.
          </p>
          <p>
            What felt good: voice notes and call-style features add immersion without feeling gimmicky. What felt
            awkward: switching between chat and media modes breaks the fantasy for a few seconds while assets load.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="pricing-in-real-use" class="review-section">
          <h3>Pricing in Real Use</h3>
          <p>
            On paper, {product.name} sits in the mid-premium tier. In practice, the free tier is usable enough to
            understand the product, but the meaningful features — better models, faster media, deeper memory — sit
            behind the paywall fast.
          </p>
          <p>
            What the pricing numbers meant for me: I would pay if chat quality is my priority; I'd hesitate if I
            mainly want unlimited image generation. The value depends on how often you actually open the app, not
            the feature list alone.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="what-stands-out" class="review-section">
          <h3>What Stands Out</h3>
          <p>
            Character depth and consistency. {product.name} does not just offer quantity — the companions feel
            differentiated, and that makes repeat sessions more interesting than swapping skins on the same bot.
          </p>
          <p>
            The overall performance score reflects that strength: this is a product built for people who want an
            ongoing relationship with a persona, not a one-off prompt toy.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="what-frustrated-me" class="review-section">
          <h3>What Frustrated Me</h3>
          <p>
            Media latency is the main friction point. When I am in a flow state chatting, waiting 10–15 seconds
            for an image pulls me out. Privacy settings also take a bit of digging — not terrible, but not as
            front-and-center as I'd prefer for this category.
          </p>
          <p>
            Minor UI nits add up: some buttons look tappable but aren't, and the upgrade prompts appear at
            emotionally bad moments (mid-conversation).
          </p>
        </section>

        <section id="final-recommendation" class="review-section">
          <h3>Final Recommendation</h3>
          <p>
            Would I keep using {product.name}? Yes — primarily for chat and character variety. I'd treat media
            as a bonus, not the main reason to subscribe.
          </p>
          <p>
            If you want a companion that feels present, remembers you, and supports longer roleplay arcs,
            {product.name} is an easy recommend. If you need fast, unlimited visual generation or the cheapest
            entry point, look elsewhere first — then come back if the conversation quality wins you over.
          </p>
        </section>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style is:global>
  .gallery-thumb-scroll {
    color: var(--color-on-surface);
  }

  [data-theme='dark'] .gallery-thumb-scroll {
    background: rgb(26 31 24 / 92%) !important;
    border-color: #2a3328 !important;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 88%);
    box-shadow: 0 2px 10px rgb(0 0 0 / 35%);
  }

  .review-article-layout {
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .review-toc {
    display: none;
  }

  @media (min-width: 1100px) {
    [data-review-article] .section-container {
      max-width: none;
      padding-left: max(1rem, calc((100vw - 720px) / 2));
      padding-right: max(1rem, calc((100vw - 720px) / 2));
      overflow: visible;
    }

    .review-article-layout {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 720px);
      justify-content: center;
    }

    .review-toc {
      display: block;
      grid-column: 1;
      grid-row: 1;
      justify-self: start;
      align-self: start;
      position: sticky;
      top: 8.5rem;
      z-index: 20;
      margin-left: calc(-56px - 12px);
      width: max-content;
      overflow: visible;
      pointer-events: none;
    }

    .review-toc__sticky,
    .review-toc__rail,
    .review-toc__toggle,
    .review-toc__drawer {
      pointer-events: auto;
    }

    .review-toc__sticky {
      position: relative;
      display: flex;
      align-items: flex-start;
      overflow: visible;
    }

    .review-article {
      grid-column: 1;
      grid-row: 1;
    }
  }

  .review-toc__rail {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    position: relative;
    z-index: 2;
  }

  .review-toc__toggle {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 44px;
    height: 44px;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-surface-variant);
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: #f5f5f5;
    color: var(--color-on-surface);
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease, background 0.15s ease;
  }

  .review-toc__toggle:hover,
  .review-toc.is-open .review-toc__toggle {
    border-color: var(--color-accent);
    color: var(--color-accent);
    background: rgb(219 39 119 / 5%);
  }

  .review-toc__drawer {
    position: absolute;
    top: 0;
    right: calc(100% + 8px);
    width: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    opacity: 0;
    border: 1px solid transparent;
    border-radius: 10px;
    background: #f5f5f5;
    transition:
      width 0.25s ease,
      opacity 0.2s ease,
      padding 0.25s ease,
      border-color 0.2s ease;
    padding: 0;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .review-toc.is-open .review-toc__drawer {
    width: 220px;
    opacity: 1;
    padding: 14px 16px;
    border-color: var(--color-surface-variant);
    pointer-events: auto;
  }

  .review-toc__title {
    margin: 0 0 10px;
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-tertiary);
    white-space: nowrap;
  }

  .review-toc__list {
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2px;
  }

  .review-toc__link {
    display: block;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    border-radius: 6px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
    text-decoration: none;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition: background 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .review-toc__link:hover,
  .review-toc__link.is-active {
    background: rgb(219 39 119 / 8%);
    color: var(--color-accent);
  }

  .prose-review {
    width: 100%;
  }

  .review-section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    scroll-margin-top: 8rem;
  }

  .review-section h3 {
    margin: 0 0 12px;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-on-surface);
  }

  .review-section p {
    margin: 0 0 14px;
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-on-surface-variant);
  }

  .review-section p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  [data-theme='dark'] .review-toc__toggle {
    background: #1a1f18;
    border-color: #2a3328;
    color: rgb(255 255 255 / 88%);
  }

  [data-theme='dark'] .review-toc__drawer {
    background: #1a1f18;
  }

  [data-theme='dark'] .review-toc.is-open .review-toc__drawer {
    border-color: #2a3328;
  }

  [data-theme='dark'] .review-toc__link:hover,
  [data-theme='dark'] .review-toc__link.is-active {
    background: rgb(219 39 119 / 12%);
  }
</style>

<script>
  function initReviewToc() {
    const root = document.querySelector('[data-review-article]');
    if (!root || root.dataset.bound === 'true') return;
    root.dataset.bound = 'true';

    const toc = root.querySelector('[data-review-toc]');
    const toggle = root.querySelector('[data-review-toc-toggle]');
    const panel = root.querySelector('[data-review-toc-panel]');
    const links = Array.from(root.querySelectorAll('[data-review-toc-link]'));
    if (!toc || !toggle || !panel) return;

    toggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const open = toggle.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
      toggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', open ? 'false' : 'true');
      panel.setAttribute('aria-hidden', open ? 'true' : 'false');
      toc.classList.toggle('is-open', !open);
    });

    links.forEach((link) => {
      link.addEventListener('click', () => {
        if (window.innerWidth < 1100) {
          toggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
          panel.setAttribute('aria-hidden', 'true');
          toc.classList.remove('is-open');
        }
      });
    });

    const headings = links
      .map((l) => document.querySelector(l.getAttribute('href') || ''))
      .filter(Boolean) as Element[];

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      (entries) => {
        entries.forEach((entry) => {
          if (!entry.isIntersecting) return;
          const id = entry.target.id;
          links.forEach((l) => {
            l.classList.toggle('is-active', l.getAttribute('href') === `#${id}`);
          });
        });
      },
      { rootMargin: '-30% 0px -55% 0px', threshold: 0 },
    );

    headings.forEach((h) => observer.observe(h));
  }

  initReviewToc();
  document.addEventListener('astro:page-load', initReviewToc);
</script>
